[0.284, "o", "\u001b[H\n \u001b[1;38;2;0;255;136myou‚ùØ \u001b[0mmap the memory then target it, i want to read the heap                                                                   \u001b[K\r\n   \u001b[48;2;204;34;0m \u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;255;255;255;48;2;204;34;0m‚¨° read_memory\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;204;34;0m \u001b[0m  \u001b[3;38;2;153;153;153mPID 264057 @ 0x555d94a3b000 ¬∑ 5153 bytes ¬∑ 98% printable\u001b[0m                                                   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[1;38;2;255;68;68mgodshell‚ùØ \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;204;204;204mThe heap is live and readable; it currently shows allocator metadata, pointers, and at least one clear string, not\u001b[m  \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mencrypted or obviously wiped. Evidence: read_memory at heap base 555d94a3b000 returned glibc-style chunk markers like 21 00\u001b[m   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m00 00 and many in-heap pointers, plus readable strings \".mo\" and \"en_US.UTF-8\".\u001b[0m                                               \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mThe first heap page is not where the interesting payload lives. Evidence: this chunk looks like locale/runtime setup data,\u001b[m    \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mwhich fits Python startup state more than script content. The better move is to walk deeper into the heap by sampling later\u001b[m   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204moffsets inside the same mapped heap region 555d94a3b000-555d94bf4000 from get_maps.\u001b[0m                                           \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mSay ‚Äúgo deeper‚Äù and I‚Äôll read a few later heap offsets to hunt for script strings, URLs, commands, or buffers.\u001b[0m                \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[1;38;2;0;255;136myou‚ùØ \u001b[0mokay, go deeper.                                                                                                         \u001b[K\r\n   \u001b[48;2;204;34;0m \u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;255;255;255;48;2;204;34;0m‚¨° read_memory\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;204;34;0m \u001b[0m  \u001b[3;38;2;153;153;153mPID 264057 @ 0x555d94a80000 ¬∑ 5153 bytes ¬∑ 98% printable\u001b[0m                                                   \u001b[K\r\n   \u001b[48;2;204;34;0m \u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;255;255;255;48;2;204;34;0m‚¨° read_memory\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;204;34;0m \u001b[0m  \u001b[3;38;2;153;153;153mPID 264057 @ 0x555d94b00000 ¬∑ 5153 bytes ¬∑ 98% printable\u001b[0m                                                   \u001b[K\r\n   \u001b[48;2;204;34;0m \u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;255;255;255;48;2;204;34;0m‚¨° read_memory\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;204;34;0m \u001b[0m  \u001b[3;38;2;153;153;153mPID 264057 @ 0x555d94b80000 ¬∑ 5153 bytes ¬∑ 98% printable\u001b[0m                                                   \u001b[K\r\n   \u001b[48;2;204;34;0m \u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;255;255;255;48;2;204;34;0m‚¨° read_memory\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;204;34;0m \u001b[0m  \u001b[3;38;2;153;153;153mPID 264057 @ 0x555d94be0000 ¬∑ 5153 bytes ¬∑ 98% printable\u001b[0m                                                   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[1;38;2;255;68;68mgodshell‚ùØ \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;204;204;204mThe heap contains Python runtime artifacts, not obvious attacker strings yet. Evidence: read_memory at\u001b[m              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m555d94b80000 exposes the socket.getaddrinfo docstring text ‚ÄúResolve host and port into list of address info entries...‚Äù,\u001b[m      \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mwhich is consistent with inspect/get_maps showing Python with socket module loaded.\u001b[0m                                           \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mLarge parts of the heap are sparse or zeroed at the sampled offsets. Evidence: 555d94b00000 and most of 555d94be0000 are\u001b[m      \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mzero-filled; 555d94a80000 looks like Python object/bytecode data and pointers, but no clear URLs, commands, or credentials\u001b[m    \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204min that window.\u001b[0m                                                                                                               \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                     "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                                                         \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mTheory: this process is using normal Python internals and the current heap samples missed script-specific buffers. Best next\u001b[m  \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mtarget is stack or the anonymous 18 MB mapping at 7f14711fe000, where live strings and decoded data often sit. If you want,\u001b[m   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mI‚Äôll read the stack next.\u001b[0m                                                                                                     \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[1;38;2;0;255;136myou‚ùØ \u001b[0mmap the memory                                                                                                           \u001b[K\r\n   \u001b[38;2;255;68;68m‚àô‚àô‚óè\u001b[0m \u001b[3;38;2;255;102;85mScanning system snapshot...\u001b[0m                                                                                             \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[1;38;2;0;255;136m‚ùØ \u001b[0m\u001b[7ma\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;240msk godshell something...\u001b[0m                                                                                                   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;85;85;85mCtrl+([r]efresh [s]ave [l]oad [p]anel) type help for more info, Esc to toggle focus\u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;68;68;68m 100%\u001b[0m                                      \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;0;255;136m[sel:bash ./launch_test_agent.sh/264057]\u001b[0m                                                                                      \u001b[K\u001b[33;H"]
