te get_maps showing a 132 KB [stack] region.\u001b[0m                                 \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mThat is abnormal enough to flag, but I can‚Äôt say why from snapshot alone. Theory: either this thread‚Äôs useful stack content\u001b[m   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204msits outside the sampled windows due to guard/lazy pages, or the snapshot exposes a zeroed view of stack memory. Memory\u001b[m       \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mreads ar"]
